label: Exeter College MS 186

metadata.label: Description
metadata.value: A manuscript which once belonged to Petrarch who possessed three copies of this text. This copy is the one most heavily annotated by him.

metadata.label: Contents
metadata.value: Julius Caesar (ff. 1r-9v). Augustus (ff. 10r-22r). Tiberius (ff. 22v-30v). Caligula (ff. 31r-38r). Claudius (ff. 38r-41v). Nero (ff. 42r-49r). Galba (ff. 49r-51v). Otho (ff. 51v-53r); Vitellius (ff. 53r-55v). Vespasian (ff. 55v-58v). Titus (ff. 58v-59v). Domitian (ff. 59v-60v).

metadata.label: Layout
metadata.value: Two columns, each 220 x c. 65-70 mm, 44 lines.

metadata.label: Hand
metadata.value: Italian gothic rotunda, punctuated by low point.

metadata.label: Decoration
metadata.value: On fol. 1r is a 21-line blank space, extending over both columns, intended for a miniature, and before each life thereafter a space for a 7-line initial, not filled in; otherwise 2-line lombards, red flourished mauve and blue flourished red. 1-line capitals in the ink of the text touched with red; blue and red paraphs.

metadata.label: Binding
metadata.value: Sewn on four bands between thin wooden boards covered with gilt brown morocco; holes on both covers showing two ties missing from each; patterned fore-edge possibly containing the arms of Jean Grolier; in the centre of the front cover is a blind roundel showing the Judgement of Paris and on the back cover a roundel containing a satyr and a woman; binding thought to have been done in Venice in 1515/16 for Lodovico Ricchieri da Rovigo, or in Milan c. 1509-15 for Jean Grolier.

metadata.label: Catalogue Description
metadata.value: Full catalogue description: Andrew Watson, A Descriptive Catalogue of the Medieval Manuscripts of Exeter College Oxford. OUP, 2000. This manuscript is also fully described by  N. Mann, 'Petrarch Manuscripts in the British Isles' Italia medioevale e umanistica, 18 (1975), 139-527, at 494-5.
